    int compare(prim a, prim b)

And in fact, this same functionality has been added to the JDK as of Java 7.  These methods don&#39;t provide arbitrary `Number` comparisons, however they give you the granularity to define any type-safe comparison you&#39;d like, by choosing which class (`Longs`, `Doubles`, etc.) to use.

